When should you use insertion sort?
    Insertion sort should be used with only a few items
    If your input is small or items are mostly sorted will be really fast.
    Use little space & it's easy to implement in code.

    Only few data & most sorted data = Insertion sort.

Bubble Sort:
    It's never good to use bubble sort, only really used for education proposes.
    Very rare to see in real life.

Selection sort:
    Same thing as bubble sort.

Merge Sort:
    Really good because of divide & conquer
    O(n log n)
    if you feel worried about worst cases cenarious you should use merge sort.
    if you wanna sort in memory on your machine and you are worried about
    space complexity merge sort is gonna be really expensive.
    space complexity --> O(n)

Quick Sort:
    Same speed of merge sort but less space complexity
    O(n log(n))
    if you are really worried about the worst case you should peak merge sort

Merge sort & quick sort are the most used sorting algorithms in real life
can we beat O(n log n)?  mathematically it's impossible to improve it.
because o(n log n) means we have to sort by comparison
all of the sorting algorithms above have to compare every number to each other.

there is one exception for this rule:
    you can improve it, if you dont make comparison.

there is a small section of inputs that we can actually beat o(n log n):
    Non-Comparison Sort:
        Counting sort
        Radix sort

they are an entire different way to think about sorting, w comparison sort
we decide the order of the numbers based on asking the question (is this bigger than another..)
non comparison sorting use the way numbers and data are stored in our computer in binary.

